# LeftNavigation

The IDS Left Nav component displays navigation items, application-specific actions, and a product logo. It gives users the ability to navigate to pre-defined areas in the product by selecting them from the navigation menu. It is designed primarily for use in the Fusion Shell.

This component is currently experimental and its API is subject to change.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/left-navigation
```

```tsx
import { LeftNavigation } from '@ids-ts/left-navigation';
```

## Props API

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `productContent` | `React.ReactNode` | No | Product-specific flex area actions/content to render above the navigaton items list |
| `footer` | `React.ReactNode` | No | Global navigation actions/content to render at the bottom |
| `logo` | `React.ReactNode` | No | Product logo to render at the bottom |
| `open` | `boolean` | No | Whether the Navigation menu is open or not |
| `anchorElementRefPropName` | `string` | No | Ref prop name if the anchor element is a custom React component. |
| `onSelect` | `(newSelectedItem: string) => void` | No | * Callback that is invoked whenever a new item is selected, with the ID of the newly selected item |
| `onClose` | `() => void` | No | - |
| `variant` | `LeftNavigationVariant` | No | * What use case the left navigation component is for. Defaults to 'unified' |
| `responsiveHeader` | `string` | No | * Header text to render above all nav items when the left nav is in responsive mode. |
| `expandedItems` | `string[]` | No | - |
| `onExpandedChange` | `(expandedItems: string[]) => void` | No | Called when expanded items change. |
| `defaultExpandedItems` | `string[]` | No | Array of itemIds that should be expanded on initial render. |

<details>
<summary>Full TypeScript Interface</summary>

```typescript
export interface LeftNavigationProps
  extends Omit<ThemeableElement<'nav'>, 'onSelect'> {
  /** Product-specific flex area actions/content to render above the navigaton items list */
  productContent?: React.ReactNode;
  /** Global navigation actions/content to render at the bottom */
  footer?: React.ReactNode;
  /** Product logo to render at the bottom */
  logo?: React.ReactNode;
  /** Whether the Navigation menu is open or not */
  open?: boolean;
  /**
   * Unique ID of the currently selected navigation item. This is used to automatically mark child items as selected
   *
   * This prop can be ignored if you prefer to manage selected items yourself.
   * ex: you have a custom wrapper around <NavigationItem /> with your own state management logic
   */
  selectedItem?: string;
  /**
   * Callback that is invoked whenever a new item is selected, with the ID of the newly selected item
   */
  onSelect?: (newSelectedItem: string) => void;
  /**
   * Callback that is invoked when the LeftNavigation is closed. This is only used for responsive mode.
   * If not specified, the component will not turn enter responsive mode at smaller screen sizes
   */
  onClose?: () => void;
  /**
   * What use case the left navigation component is for. Defaults to 'unified'
   */
  variant?: LeftNavigationVariant;
  /**
   * Header text to render above all nav items when the left nav is in responsive mode.
   */
  responsiveHeader?: string;
  /**
   * Array of itemIds that should be expanded.
   * Required when using controlled mode (when onExpandedChange is provided).
   */
  expandedItems?: string[];
  /**
   * Callback that is invoked when the expansion state changes, with an array of expanded itemIds.
   * When provided, the component operates in controlled mode and you must manage expansion state yourself.
   */
  onExpandedChange?: (
    /** Array of currently expanded itemIds */
    expandedIds: string[],
    /** Metadata about the change including the action type and affected itemId */
    meta: {
      /**
       * The action that triggered this change: 'expand' or 'collapse'
       */
      action: 'expand' | 'collapse';
      /**
       * The itemId of the item that was expanded or collapsed
       */
      itemId: string;
    }
  ) => void;
  /**
   * Uncontrolled: array of itemIds that should be expanded on initial render.
   * The component manages expansion state internally after the initial render.
   * Only used when onExpandedChange is not provided (uncontrolled mode).
   * If not provided, parent items of the selectedItem will be automatically expanded.
   */
  defaultExpandedItems?: string[];
}

export type LeftNavigationVariant = 'fusion' | 'unified';
```

</details>

